# Flutter Patterns

## Widgets
- Composition over inheritance; favor small private Widget classes
- Use `const` constructors in `build()` when possible
- Break large `build()` into smaller reusable widgets
- Use `ListView.builder` or `SliverList` for long lists (lazy loading)
- Use `compute()` for expensive work (e.g., JSON parsing) off UI thread
- No network calls or heavy computation in `build()`

## State
- Prefer `ValueNotifier` + `ValueListenableBuilder` for local state
- Use `ChangeNotifier` + `ListenableBuilder` for shared state
- This project uses Provider and GetIt; follow existing patterns

## Navigation
- Use `go_router` for declarative routing and deep links
- Use `Navigator` for dialogs and short-lived screens
